homepage.description.message: A dual-theme documentation website template built with Docusaurus 3

homepage.features.docs.description.message: Comprehensive documentation with examples, tutorials, and API references. Everything you need to get started and master your project.

homepage.features.theme.description.message: Dual theme support with elegant cream light theme and stunning starry dark theme. Seamlessly switch between themes.

homepage.features.fast.title.description: Feature title for fast and modern

homepage.features.fast.description.message: Built with modern technologies for lightning-fast performance. Responsive design that works perfectly on all devices.
homepage.features.fast.description.description: Feature description for fast and modern

homepage.features.customizable.descripti.message: Highly customizable components and themes. Easy to modify colors, fonts, layouts, and add your own branding elements.

homepage.features.mobile.description.message: Responsive design that looks great on phones, tablets, and desktop devices. Touch-friendly navigation and interactions.

homepage.features.search.description.message: Built-in search functionality to help users find content quickly. Smart search with autocomplete and suggestions.

homepage.features.subtitle.message: Everything you need to create beautiful documentation websites

homepage.architecture.title.message: Empowering Java Developers to Enter the AI Native Era

homepage.features.springIntegration.desc.message: Built on Spring AI, perfectly integrated into the Spring Boot ecosystem, ready to use out of the box

homepage.features.tongyi.description.message: Deep integration with Alibaba Cloud Tongyi Qianwen series models, providing powerful AI capabilities

homepage.features.performance.descriptio.message: Supports streaming responses and asynchronous calls, meeting high concurrency scenario requirements

homepage.features.configuration.descript.message: Rich configuration options and extension points to meet customization needs for different business scenarios

homepage.features.multimodal.description.message: Support for AI processing capabilities across multiple modalities including text, images, and voice

homepage.features.observability.descript.message: Built-in monitoring metrics and tracing capabilities to easily track AI application runtime status

homepage.acknowledgments.subtitle.message: The success of Spring AI Alibaba is built on the support of the open source community and partners

homepage.acknowledgments.springai.descri.message: Thanks to the Spring AI team for providing an excellent framework that forms a solid foundation for AI application development

homepage.acknowledgments.bailian.name.message: Alibaba Cloud Bailian Model Service Platform

homepage.acknowledgments.bailian.descrip.message: Thanks to Alibaba Cloud Bailian platform for providing powerful large model capabilities and comprehensive service support

ecosystem.subtitle.message: A comprehensive ecosystem for building intelligent applications

ecosystem.framework.description.message: Foundation frameworks for building AI-powered applications

ecosystem.product.description.message: Production-ready applications powered by our framework

ecosystem.framework.agent.description.message: Framework for building agent and multi-agent applications, with embedded context engineering support.

ecosystem.framework.graph.description.message: A low-level orchestration framework and runtime for building, managing, and deploying long-running, stateful agents.

ecosystem.framework.admin.description.message: Local visualization toolkit for the development of agent applications, supporting project management, runtime visualization, tracing, and agent evaluation.

ecosystem.framework.extensions.descripti.message: Extended implementations for Spring AI core concepts, including DashScopeChatModel, MCP registry, etc.

ecosystem.product.jmanus.description.message: A Java implementation of Manus built with Spring AI Alibaba, currently used in many applications within Alibaba Group.

ecosystem.product.dataagent.description.message: A natural language to SQL project based on Spring AI Alibaba, enabling you to query databases directly with natural language without writing complex SQL.

ecosystem.product.deepresearch.descripti.message: Deep Research implemented based on spring-ai-alibaba-graph.

codeOfConduct.description.description: The page description for code of conduct

codeOfConduct.pageDescription.message: We are committed to providing a friendly, safe and welcoming environment for all, regardless of gender, sexual orientation, disability, ethnicity, religion, or other personal characteristics.

codeOfConduct.commitmentText.message: In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming environment, we as contributors and maintainers pledge to make participation in our project and our community a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.

codeOfConduct.respectingViewpoints.message: Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences

codeOfConduct.focusingCommunity.message: Focusing on what is best for the community

codeOfConduct.showingEmpathy.message: Showing empathy towards other community members

codeOfConduct.sexualizedLanguage.message: The use of sexualized language or imagery

codeOfConduct.trollingInsults.message: Trolling, insulting or derogatory comments, and personal attacks

codeOfConduct.publishingInfo.message: Publishing others' private information without permission

codeOfConduct.otherConduct.message: Other conduct which could reasonably be considered inappropriate

codeOfConduct.enforcementText.message: Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing our standards of acceptable behavior and will take appropriate and fair corrective action in response to any behavior that they deem inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful.

codeOfConduct.reportingInstructions.message: If you encounter or witness inappropriate behavior, please contact the project team:

codeOfConduct.confidentiality.message: All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly. The project team is obligated to maintain confidentiality with regard to the reporter of an incident.

codeOfConduct.consequences.message: Project maintainers who do not follow or enforce the Code of Conduct in good faith may face temporary or permanent repercussions as determined by other members of the project's leadership.

team.pageDescription.message: We are a passionate group of developers, designers, and open source enthusiasts committed to building excellent tools for the community.

team.creatorBio.message: Passionate about creating beautiful documentation and developer experiences.

team.contributorBio.message: Loves building tools that help developers be more productive.

team.joinDescription.message: We're always looking for passionate contributors to help improve this project. Whether you're a developer, designer, writer, or just someone who loves open source, there's a place for you on our team!

codeOfConduct.commitmentText2.message: We are committed to providing a harassment-free experience for everyone participating in this project, regardless of experience level, gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, personal appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or nationality.

codeOfConduct.enforcementText2.message: By adopting this Code of Conduct, project maintainers commit to fairly and consistently applying these principles to every aspect of managing this project. Project maintainers who do not follow or enforce the Code of Conduct may be permanently removed from the project team.

codeOfConduct.enforcementText3.message: This Code of Conduct applies within all project spaces, and also applies when an individual is representing the project or its community in public spaces.

contributing.thanksText.message: Since its open source development, Spring AI Alibaba has received significant attention from the community. Every Issue and every PR from the community helps the entire project and contributes to building a better Spring AI.

contributing.thanksText2.message: We sincerely thank all developers who have submitted Issues and PRs for this project. We hope more developers from the community will join us to make the project better together.

contributing.introText.message: Before contributing code, please take a moment to understand the process for contributing code to Spring AI Alibaba.

contributing.whatText.message: We welcome any contributions at any time, whether it's simple typo corrections, bug fixes, or adding new features. Feel free to raise issues or submit PRs. We also value documentation and integration with other open source projects, and welcome contributions in these areas.

contributing.complexChanges.message: For more complex changes, it is recommended to first add a Feature label in an Issue and briefly describe the design and modification points.

contributing.mergeBeforePRText.message: Similarly, before submitting a PR, you need to rebase the code from the main branch (if your target branch is not main, then rebase the corresponding target branch). For specific operation steps, please refer to the previous chapters.

contributing.conflictResolution.message: If conflicts occur, they need to be resolved first.

contributing.codeDevelopmentText.message: Develop your own features. After development, it is recommended to use the mvn clean package command to ensure that the modified code can be compiled locally. This command also automatically formats the code in the Spring way. Then submit the code. Before submitting code, please note to create a new branch related to this feature for code submission.

contributing.qualityCheckText.message: After completing local BOE environment development, it is strongly recommended to execute the make command provided by the project tools/make for local continuous integration (CI) checks before submitting a PR to ensure that the code meets the project's standards and specifications. If you have any questions about local CI, you can type make help in the console to learn specific information.

contributing.codeStandardsText.message: To reduce some unnecessary code style issues, Spring AI Alibaba provides local Checkstyle check functionality. You can execute the mvn checkstyle:check command in the project root directory to check whether the code style meets the specifications.

contributing.codeCleaningText.message: To ensure code cleanliness, please delete unused imports in Java files. You can automatically delete unused imports by executing the mvn spotless:apply command.

contributing.codeCommitText.message: After coding is completed, you need to format & check the commit information based on the PR specification [lint-pr-title.yml](.github/workflows/lint-pr-title.yml) to ensure that the commit information meets the specifications.

contributing.commitFormat.message: Commit format: git commit -m "type(module): space compliant commit message", for example: feat(docs): contribute-zh update

contributing.prSubmissionText.message: Submit a PR, write down the modifications and implemented functions according to the Pull request template, wait for code review and merge, become a Spring AI Alibaba Contributor, and contribute to better Spring AI Alibaba.

team.rolesSectionDescription.message: Spring AI Alibaba community adopts a hierarchical role system, each role has clear responsibilities and promotion standards

team.pmc.intro.message: Project Management serves as the project management committee for Spring AI Alibaba project. Its members are individuals who have made significant contributions to the evolution and development of the Spring AI Alibaba project, including the following standards:

team.pmc.coreDev1.message: Complete design and development of multiple key modules or projects

team.pmc.commitment2.message: Actively participate in community, website, Issue, PR and other project maintenance

team.pmc.influence1.message: Has visible influence in the community

team.pmc.influence2.message: Can represent Spring AI Alibaba to participate in important conferences and events

team.pmc.mentoring1.message: Awareness of cultivating Committers and Contributors

team.pmc.election.message: Project Management Members are selected from senior Committers, discussed and voted on by all Project Management members, and require more than half of the total votes to be elected.

team.committer.intro.message: Committers are individuals with repository write permissions, including the following standards:

team.committer.contribution1.message: Able to make continuous contributions over a long period

team.committer.contribution2.message: Individuals who continuously contribute Issues and PRs

team.committer.feature1.message: Made important feature contributions to the community

team.committer.participation3.message: Host community weekly meetings and participate in sharing

team.committer.quarterly1.message: Participated in at least 1 community quarterly active contributor plan

team.committer.election.message: Committers are nominated and voted by Steering Committee members, requiring at least 3 affirmative votes to be elected.

team.contributor.intro.message: Contributors are individuals who have contributed to the project. The standard is: submitted a PR and it was merged.
